    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298938>
    dc:description "FIGURES 106–111. Head and thorax (lateral view) of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. (male unless stated). 106. C. herrero (N- T, Namibia, Amkarub 269, NMNW). 107. C. maculiventris (N-T, [Zimbabwe], Chipinda Pools, BMNH). 108. C. striatifrons (LT, Chad, Bahr el Ghazal, BMNH). 109. C. marriott sp. n. (PT, Cameroon, Kriba (beach), TAU). 110. C. moffatt sp. n. (PT, Uganda, Mujenje, HNHM). 111. C. platyphallum (♀ N-T, Liberia, 8 mi. NW Zorzor, CAS). Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298938/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298946>
    dc:description "FIGURES 130–141. Frons of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. (male unless stated). 130. C. herrero (N-T, Namibia, Amkarub 269, NMNW). 131. C. maculiventris (N-T, [Zimbabwe], Chipinda Pools, BMNH). 132. C. striatifrons (N-T, Nigeria, Gadau, BMNH). 133. C. marriott sp. n. (♀ PT, Cameroon, Kriba (beach), TAU). 134. C. moffatt sp. n. (PT, Uganda, Mujenje, HNHM). 135. C. platyphallum (♀ N-T, Liberia, 8 mi. NW Zorzor, CAS). 136. C. angolense (PT, Angola, 10 mi. NE Sá da Bandeira [= Lubango], CAS). 137. C. campsiphallum (N-T, Cameroon, Limbe (shore), TAU). 138. C. freidberg sp. n. (PT, Malawi, Viphya Mnts., TAU). 139. C. hay sp. n. (PT, Uganda, Mujenje, HNHM). 140. C. quinquevittatum (N-T, Malawi, Viphya Mnts., TAU). 141. C. sao (N-T, Nigeria, Gadau, BMNH). Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298946/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298952>
    dc:description "FIGURES 160–165. Wing of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. (male unless stated). 160. C. herrero (N-T, Namibia, Amkarub 269, NMNW). 161. C. maculiventris (N-T, S. Rhodesia [= Zimbabwe], Chipinda Pools, BMNH). 162. C. striatifrons (♀ LT, Sudan, Bal el Ghanal, BMNH). 163. C. marriott sp. n. (♀ PT, Cameroon, Kriba beach, TAU). 164. C. moffatt sp. n. (HT, Uganda, Mujenje, HNHM). 165. C. platyphallum (HT, Liberia, Robertsport, AMNH). 166–171. Scutellum of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. 166. C. herrero (same). 167. C. maculiventris (same). 168. C. striatifrons (N-T, Nigeria, Gadau, BMNH). 169. C. marriott (same). 170. C. moffatt (♀ PT, Uganda, Mujenje, HNHM). 171. C. platyphallum (same). Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298952/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298962>
    dc:description "FIGURES 218–227. Male terminalia of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. 218–220. Sternite 6 (ventral view). 218. C. marriott sp. n. (PT, Cameroon, Kriba beach, TAU). 219. C. moffatt sp. n. (PT, Uganda, Katona, HNHM). 220. C. platyphallum (HT, Liberia, Robertsport, AMNH). 221–223. Hypandrium and epandrium (lateral view). 221. C. marriott (same). 222. C. moffatt (same). 223. C. platyphallum (same). 224–227. Phallus (right lateral view). 224. C. marriott (same) [ejaculatory apodeme missing]. 225. C. moffatt (same). 226. Same, detail of serrated edge. 227. C. platyphallum (same). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298962/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298964>
    dc:description "FIGURES 228–233. Female postabdomen of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. 228. C. marriott sp. n. (lateral) (PT, Cameroon, Kriba beach, TAU). 229. Same (ventral). 230. C. moffatt sp. n. (lateral) (PT, Uganda, Katona, HNHM). 231. Same (ventral). 232. C. platyphallum (lateral) (N-T, Liberia, 8 mi. NW Zorzor, CAS). 233. Same (ventral). 234–237. Comparative material of non-Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. 234. C. helvum (lateral) (N-T, [Canada], Sandbanks P.P., Picton, DEBU). 235. Same (ventral). 236. C. anus (lateral) (N-T, Israel, Park HaYarden, TAU). 237. Same (ventral) (Figs 236, 237 after Kirk-Spriggs and Freidberg 2007: 142, figs 17, 18). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298964/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298960>
    dc:description "FIGURES 203–217. Females of Afrotropical Curtonotum spp. 203–206. Postabdomen. 203. C. maculiventris (lateral) (N-T, Nigeria, River Bagel, NMWC) [not fully distended]. 204. Same (ventral). 205. C. striatifrons (lateral) (N-T, Sudan, Roseires, MNHN) [t7 distorted]. 206. Same (ventral). 207–209. Auxiliary sclerites in region of sternite 7. 207. C. herrero. 208. C. maculiventris. 209. C. striatifrons. 210–217. Spermatheca/e of Curtonotum spp. 210. C. herrero. 211. C. maculiventris. 212. C. striatifrons. 213. C. marriott sp. n. (PT, Cameroon, Kribi (beach), TAU). 214. C. moffatt sp. n. (PT, Uganda, Katona, HNHM). 215. C. platyphallum (N-T, Liberia, 8 mi. N.W. Zorzor, CAS). 216. C. helvum (N-T, [Canada], Sandbanks P.P., Picton, DEBU). 217. C. anus (lateral) (Israel, Park HaYarden, TAU). (Figs 207–212 from Tsacas (1977), figs 5e, 12e, 11e, 5d, 12f and 11d respectively; figs 12f and 12e as C. tigrinum). Scale bars: 203–206 = 1 mm; 207–212 = 0.2 mm; 213–217 = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298960/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5298987>
    dc:description "FIGURE 324. Distribution of continental Afrotropical species of Curtonotum. Major Habitat Types: C. marriott sp. n., C. moffatt sp. n. and C. platyphallum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5298987/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

